Package oogasalad.editor.view

Class EditorGameView

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.Parent
javafx.scene.layout.Region
javafx.scene.layout.Pane
oogasalad.editor.view.EditorGameView
All Implemented Interfaces:
Styleable, EventTarget, EditorViewListener
public class EditorGameView extends Pane implements EditorViewListener
Displays a grid where visual game elements are added/updated. Implements EditorViewListener to react to model changes notified by the controller. Handles drawing, basic object selection notification, and delegates placement actions. (DESIGN-01, DESIGN-09, DESIGN-20: Observer Pattern)
Author:
Tatum McKinnis

      void redrawObjectsInternal()

      object - The EditorObject for which to draw the placeholder. Used to get type info.
      x - The x-coordinate where the placeholder should be drawn.
      y - The y-coordinate where the placeholder should be drawn.

    • resolveImagePath

      private String resolveImagePath(String path)

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the resolved URL string, or null if resolution fails

    • findResourcePath

    • redrawSprites

      private void redrawSprites(UUID id)
      Redraws the sprite associated with the specified object ID on the canvas.

      If the object or its sprite data is missing, a warning is logged and nothing is drawn. If the corresponding image is available and fully loaded, it is drawn at the object's sprite coordinates. Otherwise, a placeholder is drawn. If the object is currently selected, a visual selection indicator is also rendered.

      Parameters:
      id - the unique identifier of the object whose sprite should be redrawn

    • redrawHitboxes

      private void redrawHitboxes(UUID id)
      Redraws the hitbox of the object associated with the specified ID.

      If the object or its hitbox data is missing, a warning is logged and no hitbox is drawn. Otherwise, the hitbox is rendered as a filled rectangle using a predefined color.

      Parameters:
      id - the unique identifier of the object whose hitbox should be redrawn

    • onObjectAdded

      public void onObjectAdded(UUID objectId)
      Handles the notification that a new object has been added to the model. Adds the object's ID to the list of displayed objects, preloads its image, and ensures these operations occur on the JavaFX Application Thread. Redrawing is often implicitly triggered by a subsequent selection change.
      Specified by:
      onObjectAdded in interface EditorViewListener
      Parameters:
      objectId - The UUID of the newly added object.

    • onObjectRemoved

      public void onObjectRemoved(UUID objectId)
      Handles the notification that an object has been removed from the model. Removes the object's ID from the list of displayed objects, removes its image from the cache, and triggers a redraw to reflect the removal. Ensures these operations occur on the JavaFX Application Thread.
      Specified by:
      onObjectRemoved in interface EditorViewListener
      Parameters:
      objectId - The UUID of the removed object.

    • onObjectUpdated

      public void onObjectUpdated(UUID objectId)
      Handles the notification that an existing object's data has been updated. Preloads the object's image again (in case the sprite path changed) and triggers a redraw to reflect any visual changes (position, sprite, etc.). Ensures these operations occur on the JavaFX Application Thread.
      Specified by:
      onObjectUpdated in interface EditorViewListener
      Parameters:
      objectId - The UUID of the updated object.

    • onSelectionChanged

      public void onSelectionChanged(UUID selectedObjectId)
      Handles the notification that the currently selected object has changed. Updates the internal `selectedObjectId` state and triggers a redraw to update the visual selection indicator. Ensures these operations occur on the JavaFX Application Thread.
      Specified by:
      onSelectionChanged in interface EditorViewListener
      Parameters:
      selectedObjectId - The UUID of the newly selected object, or null if no object is selected.

    • onDynamicVariablesChanged

      public void onDynamicVariablesChanged()
      Handles the notification that dynamic variables (like game parameters) have changed. This view typically does not need to react directly to these changes.
      Specified by:
      onDynamicVariablesChanged in interface EditorViewListener

    • onErrorOccurred

      public void onErrorOccurred(String errorMessage)
      Handles the notification that an error occurred elsewhere in the editor. Logs the error message. In a more complex UI, this might update a status bar. Ensures any UI updates happen on the JavaFX Application Thread.
      Specified by:
      onErrorOccurred in interface EditorViewListener
      Parameters:
      errorMessage - A description of the error that occurred.
